WEBVTT

00:00.300 --> 00:03.934
Quorum — the Nonprofit Board OS.

00:04.234 --> 00:16.220
Stage two is the heart of the launch: the organizational board meeting. It looks long —
fifteen steps — but most of them happen in a single afternoon, in one meeting.

00:16.520 --> 00:27.954
First, hold the meeting itself. Gather all seven directors, in person or by video. The
Organizational Board Minutes double as your agenda.

00:28.254 --> 00:38.872
At that meeting, the board adopts and certifies the Bylaws — your rulebook. It's linked
right here: click Open to read it or route it for signatures.

00:39.172 --> 00:51.446
You'll also elect the officers, set the office address, confirm the fiscal year, and
confirm that directors serve without pay. Four quick decisions, all recorded in the
minutes.

00:51.746 --> 01:03.588
Then come the protection policies: conflict of interest, document retention,
whistleblower, gift acceptance, privacy — plus the criteria for who the foundation
helps.

01:03.888 --> 01:13.138
Two more items live here: approving the Get Well Soon Wellness Festival as an official
program, and ratifying anything you did before the meeting.

01:13.438 --> 01:22.664
You finish by approving and signing the Organizational Board Minutes — the official
record of it all. Ours are already fully signed.

01:22.964 --> 01:32.982
Six of fifteen done, and the rest are one good meeting away. Next: stage three —
banking, signatories, and insurance.
